        <!-- Page Title -->
        <h1 id="mt_title" class="doc-page-title">Transaction Management</h1>
        <p class="doc-page-subtitle">
          Learn how to view, filter, and manage all your transactions. Export reports for accounting, process refunds, and understand settlement cycles.
        </p>

        <!-- Section: Transaction History -->
        <section id="mt_content_history" class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="section-history">
          <h2 id="section-history" class="doc-section-title">Transaction History</h2>
          <p>
            The Transaction History screen provides a comprehensive view of all payments received through your MPay Merchant Wallet. You can access it from the main dashboard by tapping the <strong>Transactions</strong> tab.
          </p>

          <h3>Accessing Your Transactions</h3>
          <ol class="steps">
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">1</span>
              <div class="step-title">Open the MPay Merchant App</div>
              <div class="step-content">Launch the app and sign in if you haven't already.</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">2</span>
              <div class="step-title">Navigate to Transactions</div>
              <div class="step-content">Tap the <code>Transactions</code> icon in the bottom navigation bar or swipe right from the dashboard.</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">3</span>
              <div class="step-title">Browse Your History</div>
              <div class="step-content">Transactions are listed in reverse chronological order with the most recent appearing first.</div>
            </li>
          </ol>

          <h3>Filtering & Searching</h3>
          <p>
            Use the filter bar at the top of the transaction list to narrow down results. You can combine multiple filters simultaneously.
          </p>

          <!-- Filter bar mockup -->
          <div class="filter-bar-mockup">
            <div class="filter-item">
              <i class="fa fa-calendar" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              <span class="filter-item-label">Date Range:</span>
              <span>Last 30 days</span>
            </div>
            <div class="filter-item">
              <i class="fa fa-filter" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              <span class="filter-item-label">Status:</span>
              <span>All</span>
            </div>
            <div class="filter-item">
              <i class="fa fa-credit-card" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              <span class="filter-item-label">Type:</span>
              <span>QR + NFC</span>
            </div>
            <div class="filter-item">
              <i class="fa fa-search" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              <span>Search by ID, amount...</span>
            </div>
            <button class="filter-btn" aria-label="Apply filters">
              <i class="fa fa-check" aria-hidden="true"></i> Apply
            </button>
          </div>

          <p>Available filter options include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Date Range</strong> — Select predefined ranges (Today, This Week, This Month) or set a custom date range.</li>
            <li><strong>Transaction Status</strong> — Filter by Completed, Pending, Failed, or Refunded.</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Type</strong> — QR Code, NFC, or All.</li>
            <li><strong>Amount Range</strong> — Set minimum and maximum amount thresholds.</li>
            <li><strong>Search</strong> — Search by transaction ID, customer name, or reference number.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="callout callout-info">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-lightbulb" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Pro Tip</strong>
              You can save frequently used filter combinations as presets. Tap the bookmark icon in the filter bar to save your current filters.
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Transaction Details -->
        <section id="mt_content_details" class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="section-details">
          <h2 id="section-details" class="doc-section-title">Transaction Details</h2>
          <p>
            Tap any transaction in your history list to view its complete details. Each transaction record contains comprehensive information about the payment.
          </p>

          <!-- Transaction card mockup -->
          <div class="txn-card-mockup" aria-label="Example transaction detail card">
            <div class="txn-card-header">
              <span class="txn-card-id">#TXN-2025-00847</span>
              <span class="status-badge status-completed"><i class="fa fa-check-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Completed</span>
            </div>
            <div style="text-align:center;padding:12px 0;">
              <div class="txn-card-amount">$124.50</div>
            </div>
            <div class="txn-card-row">
              <span class="txn-card-label">Payment Method</span>
              <span class="txn-card-value"><i class="fa fa-qrcode" aria-hidden="true" style="margin-right:4px;"></i> QR Code</span>
            </div>
            <div class="txn-card-row">
              <span class="txn-card-label">Customer</span>
              <span class="txn-card-value">John D.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="txn-card-row">
              <span class="txn-card-label">Date & Time</span>
              <span class="txn-card-value">Mar 11, 2025 · 2:34 PM</span>
            </div>
            <div class="txn-card-row">
              <span class="txn-card-label">Fee</span>
              <span class="txn-card-value">$1.87</span>
            </div>
            <div class="txn-card-row">
              <span class="txn-card-label">Net Amount</span>
              <span class="txn-card-value" style="font-weight:700;color:#1e3a8a;">$122.63</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Understanding Transaction Statuses</h3>
          <p>Each transaction will display one of the following statuses:</p>

          <div class="doc-table-container">
            <table class="doc-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Status</th>
                  <th>Description</th>
                  <th>Action Required</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="status-badge status-completed"><i class="fa fa-check-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Completed</span></td>
                  <td>Payment has been successfully processed and funds are confirmed.</td>
                  <td>None</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="status-badge status-pending"><i class="fa fa-clock" aria-hidden="true"></i> Pending</span></td>
                  <td>Transaction is being processed. Usually resolves within 1-5 minutes.</td>
                  <td>Wait for processing</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="status-badge status-failed"><i class="fa fa-times-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Failed</span></td>
                  <td>Transaction could not be completed. Customer was not charged.</td>
                  <td>Retry payment</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="status-badge status-refunded"><i class="fa fa-undo" aria-hidden="true"></i> Refunded</span></td>
                  <td>Refund has been initiated and funds returned to the customer.</td>
                  <td>None</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h3>Transaction Detail Fields</h3>
          <p>The full transaction detail view includes the following information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Transaction ID</strong> — Unique identifier for the transaction (format: <code>TXN-YYYY-XXXXX</code>)</li>
            <li><strong>Amount</strong> — The gross payment amount</li>
            <li><strong>Fee</strong> — Processing fee deducted from the transaction</li>
            <li><strong>Net Amount</strong> — Amount you receive after fees</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Method</strong> — QR Code or NFC</li>
            <li><strong>Customer Info</strong> — Customer name (if available) and wallet reference</li>
            <li><strong>Timestamp</strong> — Exact date and time of the transaction</li>
            <li><strong>Reference Number</strong> — External reference for reconciliation</li>
            <li><strong>Settlement Batch</strong> — The settlement batch this transaction belongs to</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Refunds & Reversals -->
        <section id="mt_content_refunds" class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="section-refunds">
          <h2 id="section-refunds" class="doc-section-title">Refunds & Reversals</h2>
          <p>
            MPay Merchant Wallet supports full and partial refunds directly from the transaction detail screen. Refunds are processed back to the customer's original payment method.
          </p>

          <h3>Issuing a Full Refund</h3>
          <ol class="steps">
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">1</span>
              <div class="step-title">Open Transaction Details</div>
              <div class="step-content">Navigate to the transaction you want to refund and tap to open details.</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">2</span>
              <div class="step-title">Tap "Issue Refund"</div>
              <div class="step-content">Scroll to the bottom of the transaction details and tap the <code>Issue Refund</code> button.</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">3</span>
              <div class="step-title">Select Full Refund</div>
              <div class="step-content">Choose "Full Refund" to return the entire transaction amount to the customer.</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">4</span>
              <div class="step-title">Add a Reason (Optional)</div>
              <div class="step-content">Provide a reason for the refund. This is optional but recommended for your records.</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">5</span>
              <div class="step-title">Confirm with PIN</div>
              <div class="step-content">Enter your merchant PIN to authorize the refund. A confirmation will appear once processed.</div>
            </li>
          </ol>

          <h3>Issuing a Partial Refund</h3>
          <p>For partial refunds, follow the same steps above but select "Partial Refund" in step 3, then enter the specific amount to refund.</p>

          <div class="code-block-container">
            <div class="code-block-header">
              <span class="code-block-lang">Refund Rules</span>
              <button class="code-copy-btn" aria-label="Copy code">
                <i class="fa fa-copy" aria-hidden="true"></i> Copy
              </button>
            </div>
            <pre class="code-block">Refund Time Window:     Up to 90 days from original transaction
Partial Refund Limit:   Up to original transaction amount
Multiple Partial:       Allowed (total cannot exceed original amount)
Processing Time:        1-3 business days
Fee Refund:             Processing fees are not refunded</pre>
          </div>

          <div class="callout callout-warning">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Important</strong>
              Refunds cannot be reversed once initiated. The original processing fee is not refunded. Double-check the amount before confirming.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="callout callout-danger">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-ban" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Refund Not Available?</strong>
              Refunds are not available for transactions older than 90 days, transactions that are still in "Pending" status, or transactions that have already been fully refunded.
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Exporting Reports -->
        <section id="mt_content_export" class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="section-export">
          <h2 id="section-export" class="doc-section-title">Exporting Reports</h2>
          <p>
            Export your transaction data for accounting, tax preparation, or record-keeping purposes. MPay supports multiple export formats to fit your workflow.
          </p>

          <h3>Available Export Formats</h3>

          <div class="export-formats">
            <div class="export-format-card">
              <div class="export-icon">
                <i class="fa fa-file-csv" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="export-format-name">CSV</div>
              <div class="export-format-desc">Comma-separated values for spreadsheet applications like Excel or Google Sheets.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="export-format-card">
              <div class="export-icon">
                <i class="fa fa-file-pdf" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="export-format-name">PDF</div>
              <div class="export-format-desc">Formatted report suitable for printing or sharing with your accountant.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="export-format-card">
              <div class="export-icon">
                <i class="fa fa-file-excel" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              </div>
              <div class="export-format-name">XLSX</div>
              <div class="export-format-desc">Native Excel format with pre-formatted columns and summary calculations.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>How to Export</h3>
          <ol class="steps">
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">1</span>
              <div class="step-title">Go to Transactions</div>
              <div class="step-content">Open the Transactions screen and apply any filters you want (date range, status, etc.).</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">2</span>
              <div class="step-title">Tap the Export Button</div>
              <div class="step-content">Tap the <code><i class="fa fa-download" aria-hidden="true"></i> Export</code> button in the top-right corner of the transaction list.</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">3</span>
              <div class="step-title">Choose Format</div>
              <div class="step-content">Select your preferred format (CSV, PDF, or XLSX).</div>
            </li>
            <li class="step">
              <span class="step-number">4</span>
              <div class="step-title">Download or Share</div>
              <div class="step-content">The file will be generated and you can download it or share it directly via email.</div>
            </li>
          </ol>

          <div class="callout callout-info">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-info-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Export Limits</strong>
              You can export up to 10,000 transactions per file. For larger datasets, use the date range filter to break exports into smaller batches.
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Automated Reports</h3>
          <p>You can set up automated daily, weekly, or monthly reports that are emailed directly to your registered email address.</p>

          <div class="code-block-container">
            <div class="code-block-header">
              <span class="code-block-lang">Settings Path</span>
              <button class="code-copy-btn" aria-label="Copy code">
                <i class="fa fa-copy" aria-hidden="true"></i> Copy
              </button>
            </div>
            <pre class="code-block">Settings → Reports → Automated Reports → Enable

Schedule Options:
  • Daily   — Sent at 6:00 AM local time
  • Weekly  — Sent every Monday at 6:00 AM
  • Monthly — Sent on the 1st of each month at 6:00 AM

Format:  CSV or PDF
Email:   Your registered business email</pre>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section: Settlement Reports -->
        <section id="mt_content_settlements" class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="section-settlements">
          <h2 id="section-settlements" class="doc-section-title">Settlement Reports</h2>
          <p>
            Settlements are the process by which your transaction funds are transferred to your linked bank account. Understanding the settlement cycle helps you manage cash flow effectively.
          </p>

          <h3>Settlement Cycle</h3>
          <p>The standard settlement process follows this timeline:</p>

          <!-- Settlement timeline visual -->
          <div class="settlement-timeline" role="img" aria-label="Settlement process timeline">
            <div class="settlement-step">
              <div class="settlement-dot"><i class="fa fa-shopping-cart" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
              <div>
                <div class="settlement-label">Transaction</div>
                <div class="settlement-desc">Payment received</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="settlement-step">
              <div class="settlement-dot"><i class="fa fa-hourglass-half" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
              <div>
                <div class="settlement-label">Processing</div>
                <div class="settlement-desc">T+0 to T+1</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="settlement-step">
              <div class="settlement-dot"><i class="fa fa-layer-group" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
              <div>
                <div class="settlement-label">Batching</div>
                <div class="settlement-desc">End of day</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="settlement-step">
              <div class="settlement-dot"><i class="fa fa-university" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
              <div>
                <div class="settlement-label">Settlement</div>
                <div class="settlement-desc">T+1 to T+2</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="settlement-step">
              <div class="settlement-dot" style="background:#22c55e;"><i class="fa fa-check" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
              <div>
                <div class="settlement-label">Deposited</div>
                <div class="settlement-desc">In your bank</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Settlement Schedule</h3>
          <div class="doc-table-container">
            <table class="doc-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Plan</th>
                  <th>Settlement Frequency</th>
                  <th>Cutoff Time</th>
                  <th>Deposit Timing</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Standard</strong></td>
                  <td>Daily</td>
                  <td>11:59 PM local</td>
                  <td>Next business day (T+1)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Express</strong></td>
                  <td>Same day</td>
                  <td>3:00 PM local</td>
                  <td>Same day (T+0)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Weekly</strong></td>
                  <td>Weekly</td>
                  <td>Sunday 11:59 PM</td>
                  <td>Monday (T+1)</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <h3>Viewing Settlement Reports</h3>
          <p>Settlement reports provide a summary of all transactions included in a specific settlement batch.</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <code>Transactions → Settlements</code> tab.</li>
            <li>Select a settlement batch by date to view its details.</li>
            <li>Review the batch summary: total transactions, gross amount, total fees, and net deposit.</li>
            <li>Tap <strong>Download Report</strong> to export the settlement details.</li>
          </ol>

          <div class="callout callout-success">
            <div class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-check-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Reconciliation Tip</strong>
              Match each settlement report with your bank statement deposit to ensure all funds have been received correctly. The settlement ID appears in your bank transaction description.
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <section id="mt_faq_accordion" class="doc-section faq-section" aria-labelledby="section-faq">
          <h2 id="section-faq" class="doc-section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-1">
              <span>How far back can I view my transaction history?</span>
              <i class="fa fa-chevron-down faq-chevron" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-1" class="faq-answer" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                You can view up to 24 months of transaction history directly in the app. For older records, contact our support team to request archived data exports.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-2">
              <span>Why is my transaction still showing as "Pending"?</span>
              <i class="fa fa-chevron-down faq-chevron" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-2" class="faq-answer" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                Transactions typically move from Pending to Completed within 1-5 minutes. If a transaction remains pending for more than 30 minutes, it may indicate a processing issue. Check your internet connection and try refreshing. If the issue persists, contact support with the transaction ID.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-3">
              <span>Can I refund a transaction after the 90-day window?</span>
              <i class="fa fa-chevron-down faq-chevron" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-3" class="faq-answer" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                In-app refunds are limited to 90 days. For refunds beyond this period, you'll need to contact our support team who can process exceptional refunds on a case-by-case basis. Additional verification may be required.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-4">
              <span>How long does it take for a refund to appear in the customer's account?</span>
              <i class="fa fa-chevron-down faq-chevron" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-4" class="faq-answer" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                Refunds to MPay wallets are typically instant. Bank account refunds may take 1-3 business days depending on the customer's bank. The customer will receive a notification once the refund is processed on our end.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-5">
              <span>Can I export transactions through an API?</span>
              <i class="fa fa-chevron-down faq-chevron" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-5" class="faq-answer" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                Yes! MPay provides a REST API for programmatic access to transaction data. Visit our <strong>API Documentation</strong> for details on available endpoints, authentication, and rate limits. API access requires a Business or Enterprise plan.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-6">
              <span>Why is there a difference between the transaction amount and my settlement deposit?</span>
              <i class="fa fa-chevron-down faq-chevron" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-6" class="faq-answer" role="region">
              <div class="faq-answer-inner">
                The difference is typically due to processing fees, which are deducted before settlement. The Net Amount shown in each transaction reflects the amount after fees. Your settlement report provides a detailed breakdown of gross amounts, fees, and net deposits for each batch.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

